value.title: Trump to lift Covid-19 related travel restrictions before he leaves office, White House official says
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump is expected to lift coronavirus-related travel restrictions starting on January 26, nearly a week after he leaves office, a White House official said Monday.

value.title: GOP Lawmaker Claimed 'Democratic Machine' Paid Capitol Rioters to Make Trump Look Bad
value.excerpt: As rioters supporting President Donald Trump attacked the U.S. Capitol on January 6, newly elected Republican North Carolina Congressman Madison Cawthorn told conservative talk radio program The Charlie Kirk Show that the "Democratic machine" had placed "agitators" among the mob in order to make Trump and his followers look bad.

value.title: Acting DHS secretary: We want to leave 'no stone unturned' in securing Biden inauguration
value.excerpt: Acting Homeland Security Secretary Peter Gaynor told "America Reports" Monday that there is a "heightened sense of alert" surrounding the security preparations for Joe Biden's inauguration.

value.title: Melania Trump releases farewell message: 'It has been the greatest honor of my life'
value.excerpt: Outgoing first lady Melania Trump reflected on her four years in the White House during a farewell address to the American people on Monday.

value.title: Trump National Garden order includes statues of Whitney Houston, Kobe Bryant, Vince Lombardi, Frank Sinatra
value.excerpt: President Trump issued an executive order on Monday in which he listed dozens of "historically significant" Americans, including entertainers, founding fathers, religious figures, and others, to be featured in the new National Garden of American Heroes.

value.title: Disgraced ex-Baltimore mayor wants Trump to commute her sentence
value.excerpt: Catherine Pugh, the disgraced former Baltimore mayor convicted of using her book sales to help fund a political career, is reportedly among those seeking clemency from President Donald Trump before he leaves office.

value.title: Biden’s reported plans to kill Keystone XL pipeline alarm Canadian officials
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden is considering canceling the cross-border permit for TC energy’s Keystone XL pipeline -- and Canadian officials are worried.

value.title: Biden marks MLK Day by volunteering for hunger-relief group
value.excerpt: With an eye toward reuniting the country after the turbulent presidency of Donald Trump, President-elect Joe Biden marked the Martin Luther King Jr. federal holiday by volunteering.

value.title: Biden election legal team takes victory lap, praises help from unions, nonprofits
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden’s legal team on Monday praised help from unions and nonprofits in their efforts to ensure a secure 2020 presidential election, which led to a Biden-Harris victory.

value.excerpt: Couy Griffin, a New Mexico county official, vowed to return with firearms to the Capitol for the inauguration.

value.title: Trump, in wave of Tuesday pardons, so far not planning to pardon himself: source
value.excerpt: U.S. President Donald Trump at this point is opting not to issue a pardon for himself as he prepares an expansive list of more than 100 pardons and commutations for release on Tuesday, a source familiar with the effort said.

value.title: Biden aims to 'Make America California Again': paper
value.excerpt: The Los Angeles Times ran a headline Sunday that is sure to grab the attention of Trump supporters everywhere: “Make America California Again? That’s Biden’s plan.”

value.title: The Biden era beckons after Trump's lies and insurrection
value.excerpt: A battered nation haunted by sickness, death and division is heading into an epic week in which constitutional principles will triumph over lies and insurrection with the transfer of power from one president to the next.

value.title: Biden to nominate Gary Gensler for SEC commissioner, Rohit Chopra to lead Consumer Financial Protection Bureau
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden is expected to nominate Gary Gensler to serve as the commissioner of the Securities and Exchange Commission and Rohit Chopra to lead the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau, a source familiar with the decision tells CNN.

value.title: Pence has tried to reach Capitol Police officer who led rioters away from Senate chambers to offer thanks
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence reached out to Capitol Police officer Eugene Goodman late last week to thank him for his efforts during the attack on the US Capitol, a person close to Pence told CNN, but they haven't connected yet.

value.title: Inauguration Day 2021: Trump To Have Own 'Elaborate' Goodbye Ceremony
value.excerpt: President Trump is planning to hold a red-carpet send-off that would include a military band, a flypast by Air Force jets and a 21-gun salute on Jan. 20.

value.title: Vice President Pence thanks U.S. troops at Fort Drum
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence and his wife made their final official appearance together with a visit to Fort Drum, where they thanked the 10th Mountain Division and their families for their service

value.title: Biden transition official tells migrant caravans: 'Now is not the time' to come to US
value.excerpt: An unnamed Biden transition official told NBC News that migrants hoping to claim asylum in the U.S. during the first few weeks of the new administration "need to understand they're not going to be able to come into the United States immediately.
